The defendant failed to appear for a plea date. State requests warrant. Court authorizes warrant.
PLEA AND SENTENCING HEARING  -
At 9:58 a.m., the case is recalled.  The defendant is now present.  All parties present as before.
The Court withdraws the authorization for the warrant.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, discharge bodily fluid at public safety worker.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 2, discharge bodily fluid at public safety worker.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 5, possess THC.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read counts 3, 4, 6 and 7.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend three (3) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, commencing on 09-15-15 by 8:00 a.m.  Court authorizes transfer to Sheboygan County Jail as long as Sheboygan County Jail follow Manitowoc County Jail rules;
2) Additional three (3) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) AODA assessment and follow through;
6) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
7) Pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) provide DNA sample.  (DNA surcharges are waived);
10) obtain GED or HSED.
Minutes.
